WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:10.608
You've set your firm's rules. Now let the dashboard scan
every single move you've got and rank which ones actually
beat those rules.

2
00:00:11.208 --> 00:00:25.128
This is Best Moves to Flip. It runs every move through
your exact evaluation, sizing each one at its own tuned
target and stop. Then it hands you four different winners,
because the best move depends entirely on what you care
about most.

3
00:00:25.728 --> 00:00:40.584
Fastest Flip is pure speed. The move that passes in the
fewest days, so you can pass, withdraw, reset, and repeat.
Perfect if you're churning cheap accounts and want your
money back fast. It usually carries a higher bust rate
though, so read that number too.

4
00:00:41.184 --> 00:00:52.872
Highest Pass percent is the most reliable. The move that
clears the evaluation the most often, wasting the fewest
account fees on failed attempts. This is the one to pick
when buying resets actually hurts.

5
00:00:53.472 --> 00:01:07.344
Best EV per Account picks the most expected dollars per
attempt. Best payout efficiency, not just the highest
odds. And Consistency favors a high pass rate with steady,
even days, which fits firms that quietly punish one-big-
day trading.

6
00:01:07.944 --> 00:01:22.368
So match the winner to your situation. Cheap accounts you
can re-buy, chase Fastest Flip. Expensive resets, protect
Highest Pass. Going for funded payouts, lean on Best EV.
The dashboard already did the scanning. You just pick the
priority.

7
00:01:22.968 --> 00:01:27.168
One scan, four winners. Pick the one that fits how you
actually trade.
